could make a bigger impact the case presents the contributions that a nongovernmental organization can make in bringing about environmental change it focuses on the role that information transparency and supply chain improvements can play in reducing pollution settings china environment nonprofit organizations related ma jun and the ipe using information to improve chinas environment teaching note  reference no sitn no reviews   write a review view usage share view our pricing guide or login to see prices customers who bought this product also bought view up to ten items most often purchased with this product ref no  freitag designing a brand from nothing but waste ref no gs shanzhai bandit mobile phone companies the guerilla warfare of product development and supply chain management ref no pe car sharing in barcelona avancar ref no  amyris biotechnologies commercializing biofuel ref no gs the european recycling platform promoting competition in ewaste recycling customers who viewed this product also viewed view up to ten items most often browsed with this product ref no bm nkt photonics as doing business at the technological frontiers ref no ba asclepius consulting the sales force dilemma ref no bm cameron auto parts early internationalization ref no bmc yama ribbons  bows co ltd where to next ref no  levendary cafe the china challenge ref no bm invest or take a venture capitalists ethical dilemma ref no bac pequignet the face of the renaissance of french haute horlogerie ref no bm id fresh the way forward ref no a cardinal health inc a ref no bm launch of durra women in islamic banking your recently viewed items view up to the last ten items that you browsed fancy something different find out whats new  ref no si ma jun and the ipe using information to improve chinas environment site map about us become a member brand guidelines news our th anniversary what we do ordering coursepack creator how do i order keep up to date with email updates pricing shipping options